This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) because it proposes a new feature extraction technique for topic modeling in text documents. It also uses the Open Movie Database (OMDb) and Reuters Dataset, which are commonly used in NLP research. 

It could also belong to Information Retrieval (cs.IR) because topic modeling is often used in IR to improve search results. 

Machine Learning (cs.LG) is another likely sub-category because the paper uses the K-means algorithm for clustering and compares its results to other state-of-the-art topic models. 

Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) is also a possibility because topic modeling is a common task in AI research, and the paper proposes a new method for improving topic accuracy. 

Finally, Database (cs.DB) is a less likely but still possible sub-category because the paper deals with data preprocessing techniques for topic modeling.
